MTF,<br><br>
Always a sense of humor! &lt;G&gt; I love it! As a matter of fact, I was given a traditional Italian dinner, you know, food, food, more food, vino, more vino, sing, more sing. Real people. Real things. Real values. I forgot all about Nam for quite a while. It really did me some good!<br><br>
The Italians are a very &quot;tribal&quot; people you know. Customs differ, but the intent is the same. I now have some roots to which I can relate in a real sense in space and time. I never really had that before. It is all part of fixing this stuff in my head. I am glad to be back, though! Funny, this is home too.<br><br>
DZ<br><br>
